# The Holmatrix — Cursor Rules
# This file tells Cursor AI about the project conventions.
# Place it at the root of the repo: /coordination-app/.cursorrules

## Project Overview

The Holmatrix is a personal/family organization app at theholmatrix.com.
It is a multi-tenant app — all data is scoped by `tenant_id`.
Two core users: Aaron (aaron@thehealthcolab.com) and Michaela (mjkerrissey@gmail.com).
External collaborators can be invited to specific resources via magic link sharing.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 14+ with App Router (NOT Pages Router)
- **Language:** TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Styling:** CSS custom properties from `holmatrix-theme.css` — NO Tailwind
- **Backend:** Supabase (Postgres, Auth, RLS, Realtime, Storage)
- **Email:** Resend (for notifications, share invitations, digests)
- **Hosting:** Vercel
- **Fonts:** Google Fonts — DM Serif Display (headings) + DM Sans (body)

## Brand System — "Soft Botanica"

All colors, typography, spacing, and component tokens are defined in `src/styles/holmatrix-theme.css` as CSS custom properties prefixed with `--hm-`.

### Colors (NEVER hardcode — always use variables)
- Primary (sage green): `var(--hm-color-sage)` — buttons, links, active states
- Accent (dusty rose): `var(--hm-color-rose)` — tags, highlights, secondary actions
- Background: `var(--hm-color-cream)` — page background
- Surface: `var(--hm-color-warm-gray)` — cards, sidebar
- Text: `var(--hm-color-forest)` — primary text
- Muted text: `var(--hm-color-text-muted)` — secondary/helper text
- Border: `var(--hm-color-border)` — all borders
- Status: `var(--hm-color-success)`, `var(--hm-color-warning)`, `var(--hm-color-danger)`, `var(--hm-color-info)`

### Typography
- Headings/logo: `var(--hm-font-heading)` — DM Serif Display
- Body/UI: `var(--hm-font-body)` — DM Sans 400 + 500
- Only two weights: 400 (regular) and 500 (medium). Never use 600 or 700.

### Spacing
- Use the `--hm-space-*` scale: xs (4px), sm (8px), md (16px), lg (24px), xl (32px), 2xl (48px)

### Component Classes
The theme file provides these helper classes — use them instead of writing custom styles:
- `.hm-card` — elevated surface (white bg, border, rounded corners)
- `.hm-input` — text input fields
- `.hm-btn-primary` — primary action button (sage green)
- `.hm-btn-text` — text/link button (dusty rose)
- `.hm-label` — form labels

