## Coding Conventions

### General
- Use `"use client"` directive only on components that need browser APIs or hooks
- Prefer Server Components by default — only make components client-side when they need interactivity
- Use named exports for components, default exports only for page.tsx files
- All database queries go through Supabase client — never raw SQL in components
- Every query must include `tenant_id` filtering (RLS handles this, but be explicit)

### Component Patterns
- Components use CSS Modules (`.module.css`) that reference `--hm-*` variables
- One component per file, file name matches component name (PascalCase)
- Props interfaces defined in the same file, named `{ComponentName}Props`
- Destructure props in function signature

### Supabase Patterns
```typescript
// Always use the server client in Server Components
import { createServerClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server'

// Always use the browser client in Client Components
import { createBrowserClient } from '@/lib/supabase/client'

// Queries always filter by tenant — RLS enforces this but be explicit
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('tasks')
  .select('*, projects(name)')
  .eq('tenant_id', tenantId)
  .order('created_at', { ascending: false })
```

### Table / Column Filter Pattern
All table views (Tasks, Documents, Recipes, Recs) share the same UX:
- Clickable column headers open a dropdown with sort options + filter checkboxes
- Excel-style interaction — familiar to non-technical users
- Search bar + "New" button in the page header
- Rows are clickable to navigate to detail page

### Mobile Responsiveness
- Primary usage is MOBILE — design mobile-first
- Navigation becomes bottom tab bar on screens < 768px
- Tables collapse non-essential columns on mobile:
  - Tasks: show task name + status dot + assignee avatar. Hide due date, priority, project.
  - Documents: show name + category badge. Hide project, date, author.
  - Recipes/Recs: show name + type badge. Hide source, date, author.
- Collapsed data is visible when user taps a row (detail view)
- Grocery list is already mobile-optimized (checklist format)

### Markdown Editor
- Use Tiptap or Milkdown library
- NO toolbar — clean editing surface
- "Use markdown" text hint that shows a hover cheat sheet (20 common commands)
- Used in task detail pages for the description field

## Authentication Flow

1. Login page shows email/password form with magic link toggle
2. Email/password = core family users (Aaron, Michaela)
3. Magic link = approved external collaborators
4. Supabase Auth handles both flows
5. On signup, a trigger auto-creates the profile row with tenant_id
6. Middleware redirects unauthenticated users to /login
7. After login, redirect to /dashboard

## Do NOT

- Do not use Tailwind CSS — this project uses CSS custom properties
- Do not hardcode colors — always use `var(--hm-*)` tokens
- Do not use font-weight 600 or 700 — only 400 and 500
- Do not use the Pages Router — this is App Router only
- Do not install shadcn/ui — we have our own component system
- Do not put `"use client"` on components that don't need it
- Do not skip TypeScript types — everything should be typed
- Do not create API routes when a Server Component can do the job
